#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:4
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command"
msgstr "Ukaz"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:6
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &partman; commands are what <link linkend=\"glossary-job\">jobs</link> "
"are made up of. These are very low level steps being taken, often executed "
"by an external tool, and only visible in the detailed progress report."
msgstr ""
"V &partman; so ukazi tisto, iz česar so sestavljena <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"job\">opravila</link>. To so koraki na zelo nizki ravni, ki jih pogosto "
"izvaja zunanje orodje in so vidni le v podrobnem poročilu o napredku."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "The user normally does not have to bother with commands at all."
msgstr "Uporabniku se običajno sploh ni treba ukvarjati z ukazi."

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:11
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-operation\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-job\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-operation\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-job\"></glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:18
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cylinder"
msgstr "Cilinder"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:20
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A unit used to divide up a <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">device</link>. "
"Some operating systems and many disk tools require <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"partition\">partitions</link> to begin and end on a cylinder. &partman; "
"therefore automatically snaps partitions to cylinder boundaries when "
"changing their start or end."
msgstr ""
"Enota, ki se uporablja za razdelitev <link linkend=\"glossary-device"
"\">naprave</link>. Nekateri operacijski sistemi in mnoga diskovna orodja "
"zahtevajo, da se <link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">particije</link> "
"začnejo in končajo na cilindru. &partman; zato samodejno pripne particije na "
"meje cilindra, ko spremeni njihov začetek ali konec."

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-head\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-sector\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-head\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-sector\"></glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:29
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cylinder Size"
msgstr "Velikost cilindra"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:31
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The number of <link linkend=\"glossary-sector\">sectors</link> per <link "
"linkend=\"glossary-cylinder\">cylinder</link> on a <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"device\">device</link>. Calculated as the number of <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"head\">heads</link> multiplied by the number of <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"sector\">sectors</link> per track."
msgstr ""
"Število <link linkend=\"glossary-sector\">sektorjev</link> na <link linkend="
"\"glossary-cylinder\">cilinder</link> v <link linkend=\"glossary-device"
"\">napravi</link >. Izračunano kot število <link linkend=\"glossary-head"
"\">glav</link>, pomnoženo s številom <link linkend=\"glossary-sector"
"\">sektorjev</link> na sled."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:38
#, no-c-format
msgid "Device"
msgstr "Naprava"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:40
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A physical disk device. Physical disk devices are divided into logical "
"sections called <link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">partitions</link> with "
"the use of <link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\">partition tables</link>."
msgstr ""
"Fizična diskovna naprava. Fizične diskovne naprave so razdeljene na logične "
"odseke, imenovane <link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">particije</link>, z "
"uporabo <link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\">tabel particij</link>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disk Label"
msgstr "Oznaka diska"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Another name for a <link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\">partition "
"table</link> stemming from the SUN/BSD world."
msgstr ""
"Drugo ime za <link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\">tabelo particij</"
"link> izhaja iz sveta SUN/BSD."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:54
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"They are easy to mix up, but a disk label has nothing to do with a <link "
"linkend=\"glossary-filesystemlabel\">file system label</link>."
msgstr ""
"Lahko jih je pomešati, vendar oznaka diska nima nobene zveze z <link linkend="
"\"glossary-filesystemlabel\">oznako datotečnega sistema</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See <ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BSD_disklabel\">this Wikipedia "
"entry</ulink> for details on the name."
msgstr ""
"Za podrobnosti o imenu glejte <ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"BSD_disklabel\">ta vnos v Wikipediji</ulink>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid "Extended Partition"
msgstr "Razširjena particija"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">partition</link> that contains other "
"partitions. Extended partitions can only be <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"primarypartition\">primary partitions</link> themselves. Whether extended "
"partitions are available or not depends on the <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"partitiontable\">partition table</link> type used. MS-DOS partition tables "
"allow one extended partition per <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">device</"
"link>."
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">Particija</link>, ki vsebuje druge "
"particije. Razširjene particije so lahko same samo <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"primarypartition\">primarne particije</link>. Ali so razširjene particije na "
"voljo ali ne, je odvisno od uporabljene vrste <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"partitiontable\">tabele particij</link>. Tabele particij MS-DOS dovoljujejo "
"eno razširjeno particijo na <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">napravo</link>."

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-primarypartition\"></glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-logicalpartition\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-primarypartition\"></glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-logicalpartition\"></glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "File System"
msgstr "Datotečni sistem"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:80
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A file system defines how the storage of data (files with their metadata, "
"folders and their metadata, free space) is organized within a <link linkend="
"\"glossary-partition\">partition</link>. There are various different types "
"of file systems, some coming originally from the Unix/Linux world, some not. "
"Examples for commonly used file systems on Unix/Linux are Btrfs, ext4 and "
"XFS."
msgstr ""
"Datotečni sistem določa, kako je shranjevanje podatkov (datoteke z njihovimi "
"metapodatki, mape in njihovi metapodatki, prosti prostor) organizirano "
"znotraj <link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">particije</link>. Obstaja "
"veliko različnih vrst datotečnih sistemov, nekateri izvirajo iz sveta Unix/"
"Linux, nekateri ne. Primeri pogosto uporabljenih datotečnih sistemov v Unixu/"
"Linuxu so Btrfs, ext4 in XFS."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "File System Label"
msgstr "Oznaka datotečnega sistema"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:89
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A title of a file system. Some file systems (among them Btrfs, ext2/3/4, "
"FAT16/32 and NTFS) support setting a label for the file system so it can be "
"identified in tools like &partman; or other applications."
msgstr ""
"Naslov datotečnega sistema. Nekateri datotečni sistemi (med njimi Btrfs, "
"ext2/3/4, FAT16/32 in NTFS) podpirajo nastavitev oznake za datotečni sistem, "
"tako da ga je mogoče prepoznati v orodjih, kot je &partman; ali druge "
"aplikacije."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:94
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"They are easy to mix up, but a file system label has nothing to do with a "
"<link linkend=\"glossary-disklabel\">disk label</link>."
msgstr ""
"Zlahka jih je pomešati, vendar oznaka datotečnega sistema nima nobene zveze "
"z <link linkend=\"glossary-disklabel\">oznako diska</link>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid "Flag"
msgstr "Zastavica"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossterm>GPT</glossterm>"
msgstr "<glossterm>GPT</glossterm>"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A modern partition table format supported by most modern computers and "
"operating systems. It supports more than 4 <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"primarypartition\">primary partitions</link> unlike older MS-DOS partition "
"table."
msgstr ""
"Sodoben format tabele partici, ki ga podpira večina sodobnih računalnikov in "
"operacijskih sistemov. Podpira več kot 4 <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"primarypartition\">primarne particije</link> za razliko od starejše tabele "
"particij MS-DOS."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid "Head"
msgstr "Glava"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A unit used to divide up a <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">device</link>."
msgstr ""
"Enota, ki se uporablja za razdelitev <link linkend=\"glossary-device"
"\">naprave</link>."

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:118
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-cylinder\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-sector\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-cylinder\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-sector\"></glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:125
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossterm>Job</glossterm>"
msgstr "<glossterm>Opravilo</glossterm>"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &partman; a number of jobs is what <link linkend=\"glossary-operation"
"\">operations</link> are made up of. You normally do not have to bother with "
"jobs at all; it only becomes apparent when applying the list of pending "
"operations: &partman; will then show a progress dialog that is made up of "
"all operations and their jobs and show which operation and which job is "
"currently being executed."
msgstr ""
"V &partman; <link linkend=\"glossary-operation\">operacije</link> so "
"sestavljene iz številnih opravil. Običajno se vam z opravili sploh ni treba "
"obremenjevati; postane razvidno šele pri uporabi seznama čakajočih operacij: "
"&partman; bo nato prikazal pogovorno okno napredka, ki je sestavljeno iz "
"vseh operacij in njihovih opravil ter pokazalo, katera operacija in katero "
"opravilo se trenutno izvaja."

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-operation\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-command\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-operation\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-command\"></glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:136
#, no-c-format
msgid "Label"
msgstr "Oznaka"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Either a <link linkend=\"glossary-disklabel\">disk label</link> or a <link "
"linkend=\"glossary-filesystemlabel\">file system label</link>."
msgstr ""
"Bodisi <link linkend=\"glossary-disklabel\">oznaka diska</link> ali <link "
"linkend=\"glossary-filesystemlabel\">oznaka datotečnega sistema</link>."

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-disklabel\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-filesystemlabel\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-disklabel\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-filesystemlabel\"></glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:147
#, no-c-format
msgid "Logical Partition"
msgstr "Logična particija"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">partition</link> inside an <link "
"linkend=\"glossary-extendedpartition\">extended partition</link>."
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">Particija</link> znotraj <link linkend="
"\"glossary-extendedpartition\">razširjene particije</link>."

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:151
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-primarypartition\"></glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-extendedpartition\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-primarypartition\"></glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-extendedpartition\"></glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:158
#, no-c-format
msgid "LUKS"
msgstr "LUKS"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "Linux Unified Key Setup is the standard encryption format for Linux."
msgstr "Linux Unified Key Setup je standardni format šifriranja za Linux."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:166
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossterm>LVM</glossterm>"
msgstr "<glossterm>LVM</glossterm>"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:168
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"LVM is a system for managing logical partitions that is more flexible than "
"normal partitions. It consists of three main components:"
msgstr ""
"LVM je sistem za upravljanje logičnih particij, ki je bolj prilagodljiv kot "
"običajne particije. Sestavljen je iz treh glavnih komponent:"

#. Tag: member
#: glossary.docbook:170
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"LVM physical volumes are partitions on the disk whose space is managed by "
"LVM."
msgstr ""
"Fizični nosilci LVM so particije na disku, katerih prostor upravlja LVM."

#. Tag: member
#: glossary.docbook:171
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"LVM volume group is a collection of LVM physical volumes that can be "
"partitioned into logical partitions. It might be used to create file systems "
"spanning over multiple devices or to split encrypted <link linkend="
"\"glossary-luks\">LUKS</link> volume into smaller partitions."
msgstr ""
"Skupina nosilcev LVM je zbirka fizičnih nosilcev LVM, ki jih je mogoče "
"razdeliti na logične particije. Lahko se uporablja za ustvarjanje datotečnih "
"sistemov, ki zajemajo več naprav, ali za razdelitev šifriranega nosilca "
"<link linkend=\"glossary-luks\">LUKS</link> na manjše particije."

#. Tag: member
#: glossary.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"LVM logical volumes are similar to normal partitions except that they reside "
"on LVM volume group. Also, the location of LVM logical partitions does not "
"matter and they do not have to be physically contiguous. Therefore, "
"&partman; does not allow to move LVM logical volumes and displays the "
"remaining free space at the end of the device."
msgstr ""
"Logični nosilci LVM so podobni običajnim particijam, le da se nahajajo v "
"skupini nosilcev LVM. Tudi lokacija logičnih particij LVM ni pomembna in ni "
"nujno, da so fizično sosednje. Zato &partman; ne dovoljuje premikanja "
"logičnih nosilcev LVM in prikaže preostali prosti prostor na koncu naprave."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:178
#, no-c-format
msgid "Operation"
msgstr "Operacija"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:180
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&partman; divides the work it does into operations, <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"job\">jobs</link> and <link linkend=\"glossary-command\">commands</link>."
msgstr ""
"&partman; razdeli delo, ki ga opravlja, na operacije, <link linkend="
"\"glossary-job\">opravila</link> in <link linkend=\"glossary-command"
"\">ukaze</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:183
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Operations are the most visible of the three. If you pick an action in the "
"graphical user interface, this will likely result in a new operation being "
"added to the list of pending operations. The idea behind that is: You will "
"most probably want to set up quite a number of steps to transform the "
"current state of your disk devices to the state you have in mind. Some of "
"these steps may take quite a long time to execute (like copying a large file "
"system or resizing a file system that is nearly full). To save you from "
"having to sit in front of your computer for a long time waiting for one step "
"to finish and then starting the next one, operations allow you to exactly "
"specify how the computer's devices should look like once everything is "
"finished, then let &partman; apply the operations and come back when it has "
"executed all of them."
msgstr ""
"Operacije so najbolj vidne od treh. Če izberete dejanje v grafičnem "
"uporabniškem vmesniku, bo to verjetno povzročilo dodajanje nove operacije na "
"seznam čakajočih operacij. Ideja za tem je: Najverjetneje boste želeli "
"nastaviti kar nekaj korakov za pretvorbo trenutnega stanja vaših diskovnih "
"naprav v stanje, ki ga imate v mislih. Izvedba nekaterih od teh korakov "
"lahko traja precej dolgo (na primer kopiranje velikega datotečnega sistema "
"ali spreminjanje velikosti datotečnega sistema, ki je skoraj poln). Da vam "
"ne bi bilo treba dolgo časa sedeti pred računalnikom in čakati, da se en "
"korak konča in nato začnete z naslednjim, vam operacije omogočajo, da "
"natančno določite, kako naj izgledajo naprave računalnika, ko je vse "
"končano, nato pa pustite &partman; uporabi operacije in se vrne, ko jih "
"izvede vse."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:186
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Operations are kept in a list of pending operations. As long as an operation "
"has not been applied it can still be <link linkend=\"menu-edit-undo\">taken "
"back easily</link> and nothing will have been modified."
msgstr ""
"Operacije so shranjene na seznamu čakajočih operacij. Dokler operacija ni "
"bila uporabljena, jo je še vedno mogoče <link linkend=\"menu-edit-undo"
"\">preprosto prevzeti nazaj</link> in nič ne bo spremenjeno."

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-job\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-command\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-job\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-command\"></glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:195
#, no-c-format
msgid "Partition"
msgstr "Particija"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:197
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A section of a <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">hard disk device</link> "
"that can hold a <link linkend=\"glossary-filesystem\">file system</link> or "
"other partitions. Without at least one valid partition, a disk can not be "
"used."
msgstr ""
"Razdelek <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">naprave trdega diska</link>, ki "
"lahko vsebuje <link linkend=\"glossary-filesystem\">datotečni sistem</link> "
"ali druge particije. Brez vsaj ene veljavne particije diska ni mogoče "
"uporabiti."

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-device\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-partitiontable\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-primarypartition\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-extendedpartition\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-logicalpartition\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-device\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-partitiontable\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-primarypartition\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-extendedpartition\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-logicalpartition\"></glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:209
#, no-c-format
msgid "Partition Flag"
msgstr "Zastavica particije"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:211
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A marker for a <link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">partition</link>. The "
"availability of these flags depends on the type of <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"partitiontable\">partition table</link> used."
msgstr ""
"Oznaka za <link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">particijo</link>. "
"Razpoložljivost teh zastavic je odvisna od vrste uporabljene <link linkend="
"\"glossary-partitiontable\">tabele particij</link>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:218
#, no-c-format
msgid "Partition Table"
msgstr "Tabela particij"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A small section at the beginning of a <link linkend=\"glossary-device"
"\">device</link> used to store information about the layout of the device's "
"<link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">partitions</link>. There are different "
"types of partition tables, each with their own limitations."
msgstr ""
"Majhen razdelek na začetku <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">naprave</link>, "
"ki se uporablja za shranjevanje informacij o postavitvi <link linkend="
"\"glossary-partition\">particij</link> naprave. Obstajajo različne vrste "
"tabel particij, od katerih ima vsaka svoje omejitve."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:223
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sometimes also referred to as <quote>disk label</quote>."
msgstr "Včasih se imenuje tudi <quote>oznaka diska</quote>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:230
#, no-c-format
msgid "Primary Partition"
msgstr "Primarna particija"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:232
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">partition</link> directly inside a "
"<link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\">partition table</link>, as opposed "
"to <link linkend=\"glossary-logicalpartition\">logical partitions</link>, "
"which are in <link linkend=\"glossary-extendedpartition\">extended "
"partitions</link>."
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">Particija</link> neposredno znotraj "
"<link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\">tabele particij</link>, v "
"nasprotju z <link linkend=\"glossary-logicalpartition\">logičnimi "
"particijami</link>, ki so v <link linkend=\"glossary-extendedpartition"
"\">razširjenih particijah</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:235
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\">Partition tables</link> usually "
"impose restrictions on the maximum number of primary partitions that can be "
"created on a <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">device</link>. For MS-DOS "
"type partition tables, for example, this maximum number is four."
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\">Tabele particij</link> običajno "
"nalagajo omejitve največjega števila primarnih particij, ki jih je mogoče "
"ustvariti v <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">napravi</link>. Za tabele "
"particij tipa MS-DOS je na primer to največje število štiri."

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-extendedpartition\"></glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-logicalpartition\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-extendedpartition\"></glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-logicalpartition\"></glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:244
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sector"
msgstr "Sektor"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:246
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A unit used to divide up a <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">device</link>. "
"<link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">Partitions</link> must always begin and "
"end on a sector."
msgstr ""
"Enota, ki se uporablja za razdelitev <link linkend=\"glossary-device"
"\">naprave</link>. <link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">Particije</link> se "
"morajo vedno začeti in končati na sektorju."

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:248
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-head\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-cylinder\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-head\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-cylinder\"></glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:255
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sector Size"
msgstr "Velikost sektorja"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:257
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The number of bytes per <link linkend=\"glossary-sector\">sector</link> on a "
"<link linkend=\"glossary-device\">device</link>. The sector size of most "
"devices in use today is 512 bytes."
msgstr ""
"Število bajtov na <link linkend=\"glossary-sector\">sektor</link> v <link "
"linkend=\"glossary-device\">napravi</link>. Velikost sektorja večine "
"današnjih naprav je 512 bajtov."
